                            <origDate>eighth to ninth century</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found">Also known as the Maiden stone or the Drumdurno stone, the ogham was not discovered until the 2000s and the inscription was first mentioned in <date>2017</date> (Barnes 2017, 2-3). The stone was first recorded in <date>1726</date> (Gordon 1726, 59) and first illustrated in <date>1788</date> (Cordiner 1788, 33). It has been suggested that the stone was moved from its original location a few yards westwards around <date cert="low">1866</date> to allow for the construction of a road (Barnes 2017, 4).  
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed" when="2022-05-19">Recorded beside a minor road at NJ 70378 24714 on <date>May 19th 2022</date>.
                        </provenance>
