            <div type="commentary">
                 <list type="witDetail">
                     <item n="1"><p>Barnes suggest the slab likely <q>had a role of a prayer cross or boundary marker and would have been erected under elite patronage – secular or ecclesiastical aristocracy</q> (Barnes 2017, 5). There are also numerous mythological stories associated with the carved stone (ibid).</p>
                     </item>
                     <item n="2"><p>Information about the ogham inscription and its analysis is limited due to the lack of publications.</p>
                     </item>
                 </list>
